                                THE MAIN SCREEN

THIS IS THE SCREEN VIA WHICH THE MAJORITY OF YOUR ACTIONS ARE CARRIED OUT.
ALTHOUGH AT FIRST IT MIGHT LOOK VERY COMPLICATED, IN REALITY A QUICK GUIDED 
OUR SHOULD BE MORE THAN SUFFICIENT IN SHOWING YOU HOW TO FIND YOUR WAY AROUND
THE GAME.

THE SCREEN CAN BE SUBDIVIDED INTO FOUR MAIN HORIZONTAL SECTIONS WHICH ARE FROM
TOP TO BOTTOM..

(A) TOP OF SCREEN FROM LEFT TO RIGHT        - THE ENVIROMENT AND GRAPHIC ICONS

(B) JUST BELOW (A) AGAIN LEFT TO RIGHT      - THE MONITORS

(C) MIDDLE OF THE SCREEN FROM LEFT TO RIGHT - THE MAIN MODULE

(D) BOTTOM OF THE SCREEN FROM LEFT TO RIGHT  - THE DIRECTION ICON


THE ENVIROMENT AND GRAPHIC ICONS [A] [TOP OF SCREEN HORIZONTAL LEFT TO RIGHT]
--------------------------------
THESE ICONS ALLOW THE PLAYER TO AFFECT THE WAY THE GAME LOOKS ON SCREEN, AND 
TO CARRY OUT CERTAIN ACTIONS, THE THREE ICONS ON THE (TOP) LEFT ARE ENVIROMENT
ICONS, AND ALLOW THE LAYOUT OF THE SCREEN TO BE CHANGED AS DESIRED. FROM THE
STANDARD SCREEN TO TEXT ONLY SCREEN, FOR EXAMPLE. F1/F2/F3 WILL ALSO ACTIVATE
THESE SCREENS. AND YOU SHOULD EXPERIMENT WITH THEM TO DECIDE ON THE SCREEN
LAYOUT YOU PRFER. THE RIGHT THREE ICONS(TOP) RIGHT ARE GRAPHICS ICONS. THESE
ARE FROM LEFT TO RIGHT, FOR THE MAP SYSTEM, LOCATION GRAPHICS AND INTERACTIVE
PUZZLES. AGAIN F4/F5/F6 WILL ACTIVATE THEM. THE MAP SYSTEM ICON, WHICH IS ONLY
AVAILABLE WHEN YOU ARE ON BOARD YOUR SHIP, IS EXPLAINED IN MORE DETAIL LATER.
THE OTHER GRAPHICS ICONS WILL FLASH AND BLEEP WHEN THERE IS A RELEVANT PUZZLE
TO BE SOLVED.IF, FOR EXAMPLE YOUR CURRENT LOCATION HAS AN ILLUSTRATION, OR
THERE IS AN INTERACTIVE PUZZLE TO BE COMPLETED THE APPROPRIATE ICON WILL FLASH
AND A BLEEP WILL SOUND NOTIFYING YOU OF THIS.

MONITORS [B] JUST BELOW [A] HORIZONTAL LEFT TO RIGHT
--------
BELOW THE ENVIROMENT AND GRAPHICS ICONS ARE THE MONITORS WHICH DISPLAY 
PICTURES OF ALL THE CHARACTERS IN THE CURRENT LOCATION. EACH INDIVIDUAL 
MONITOR CAN BE TURNED ON/OFF BY PLACING THE MOUSE POINTER OVER THE LITTLE 
SWITCH ON THE TOP LEFT HAND CORNER OF EACH, OR BY USING F7/F8/F9.

ICON DRIVER [C] HORIZONTAL LEFT TO RIGHT - MIDDLE OF THE SCREEN - ]
-----------
BENEATH THE MONITORS AND TO THE LEFT HAND SIDE OF THE SCREEN IS THE ICON
DRIVER. THE DISPLAY VARIES ACCORDING TO THE SPCAE AVAILABLE. A SCROLL BAR
(SHOWN WITH UP/DOWN CURSOR) ENABLES YOU TO SCROLL UP/DOWN THE LIST IN PAGES OR
ITEM-BY-ITEM. THE ICON DRIVER IS HIERARCHICAL, IN THAT  COMMANDS ARE BUILT UP
SEQUENTIALLY. THERE ARE THREE MAIN DISPLAYS; ACTION ICONS PRIMARILY, THEN AN
ITEM LIST AND THEN A PREPOSITION LIST.

INITIALLY THE ICON DRIVER IS AT THE TOP MOST LEVEL, DISPLAYING THE ICONS
REPRESENTING ALL THE CURRENT ACTIONS AVAILABLE. CLICKING ON AN ACTION ICON
BRINGS UP A LIST OF ITEMS WHICH ARE RELEVANT TO THE ACTION AND THE SITUATION 
OF THE PLAYER.SO, FOR EXAMPLE, SHOULD YOU CLICK ON THE `OPEN` ICON, A LIST OF
ALL OPENABLE OBJECTS IN YOUR CURRENT LOCATION WILL BE PRESENTED. IF YOU CLICK
ON AN `ACTION` ICON AND NOTHING HAPPENS, THEN THAT ACTION IS CURRENTLY NOT
AVAILABLE.IF, FOR EXAMPLE, YOU CLICKED ON `OPEN` AND THERE IS NOTHING TO
`OPEN`, THEN THE ICON WILL BE IN-ACTIVE.

THE SENTENCE WHICH IS BEING CONSTRUCTED IS DISPLAYED AT THE TOP OF THE WINDOW.
THIS LINE WILL INFORM YOU OF THE ACTION WHICH ANY ICON WILL CARRY OUT, SHOULD
YOU BE UNSURE AS TO WHAT A PARTICULAR ICON IS.IF YOU CLICK ON IT, THE ACTION
ITS CARRIES OUT WILL BE DISPLAYED HERE.

BELOW THE CURRENT SENTENCE IS A LIST OF ITEMS, CONSISTING OF AN ICON, AND
THE THE ITEM NAME. AN ITEM CAN BE SELECTED BY CLICKING ON EITHER THE ITEM 
ICON OR THE ITEM NAME.

SOME ACTIONS ALLOW PREPOSITIONS SUCH AS IN/ON/UNDER/WITH ect..AND THESE CAN 
COME BEFORE OR AFTER AN ITEM. AN `EXECUTE` OPTION WILL DO JUST THAT; EXECUTE
THE CURRENT COMMAND WITHOUT USING FURTHER PREPOSITION WORDS. SO SHOULD THERE 
BE CHOICE, FOR EXAMPLE; `SEARCH DRAWERS IN THE RED DESK`, WHERE THE FIRST.
SEARCHES ALL THE DRAWERS IN THE RED DESK, IN ORDER TO CARRY OUT THE BRIEFER
COMMAND FROM THE ICON MENU, YOU WOULD NEED TO END IT WITH THE `EXECUTE`
COMMAND. ALSO, MANY ACTIONS YOU WILL WANT TO CARRY OUT WILL HAVE TWO ITEMS,
WITH A PREPOSITION SEPERATING THEM.SO, FOR EXAMPLE, YOU COULD `PUT BAG IN
CUPBOARD` THE ICON DRIVER AUTOMATICALLY HANDLES THE SEQUENCE OF
ACTION-ITEM-PREPOSITION-ITEM. AT ANY STAGE, YOU CAN USE THE `CANCEL`OPTION TO
RETURN TO THE ACTION ICON LIST. ALL THIS MIGHT MAKE USING THE ICON INTERFACE
SOUND VERY COMPLICATED, BUT AFTER A FEW MINUTES EXPERIMENTING WITH THE ICONS
AND THEIR EFFECTS, YOU SHOULD FIND THEM EXTREMELY CONVENIENT AND EASY TO USE.
CONSIDER THIS PRACTICAL EXAMPLE. THE FIRST ACTION YOU MUST CARRY OUT IN THE
GAME IS TO `PUSH PAD`,SO,FIRST OF ALL, FIND THE ICON FOR `PUSH`. WHICH IS THE
FIFTH ICON DOWN ON THE LEFT HAND SIDE. CLICK ON THIS, AND THE WORD PUSH WILL
APPEAR AT THE TOP OF THE ICON PANEL. THE ICONS WILL NOW BE REPLACED WITH A 
LIST OF OBJECTS YOU CAN PUSH. SELECT THE PAD AND THEN CLICK ON THE `EXECUTE`
ICON. SIMPLE AS THAT...

